    "claude-sonnet-4-6": "Exceptional depth and clinical accuracy throughout. Provides the full Leipzig scoring system with exact thresholds and scoring weights — a critical diagnostic tool absent in all other models. Correctly distinguishes ceruloplasmin as an acute-phase reactant that can be falsely normal. Accurately notes that neurological WD can paradoxically worsen with chelation initiation (~20-50% with penicillamine), a critical safety point missed by all others. Correctly identifies tetrathiomolybdate as an emerging option for acute neurological WD. Specifies that neuropsychiatric WD alone is not a standard transplant indication. Includes pediatric dosing caveats, pregnancy management note, and family screening protocol. Uncertainty handling is exemplary — explicitly flags missing case data while still providing actionable population-level guidance. Structure is superior with tables, code blocks, and clear visual hierarchy. Minor gap: does not specify the Revised Wilson Index for transplant prognostication in ALF.",
